<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_BuildMode_Building_RoomsWalls" s="316030">
  <T n="name">0x73664507<!--String: "Rooms & Walls"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\BuildMode\BuildMode_RoomsAndWalls_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:cb4fcdf4ce1cebad</T>
      <T n="text">0x50E43F41<!--String: "<b><font color='#199C2C'>Rooms</font></b> are the most basic components of a building. A Room is a <b><font color='#199C2C'>space</font></b> usually <b><font color='#199C2C'>enclosed by Walls</font></b>, but it could also be enclosed by Fences (like a porch or balcony) or nothing at all.\n\nYou can find all the tools to create Rooms and Walls in the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Walls and Empty Rooms</font></b> catalog."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\BuildMode\BuildMode_RoomsAndWalls_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:cb4fcdf4ce1cebae</T>
      <T n="text">0xA8582C67<!--String: "There are many ways to <b><font color='#199C2C'>create</font></b> a new Room.\nClick and drag with the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Wall Tool</font></b> to place a Wall. Walls can be placed along the grid, or diagonally. Once you have enclosed a space in Walls, it becomes a Room. \n\nTo create a rectangular Room in one click and drag motion, hold down [Shift] on the keyboard while using the Wall Tool, or use the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Room Tool</font></b>.\n\nThe total <b><font color='#199C2C'>cost</font></b> of the Room is displayed above the cursor."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\BuildMode\BuildMode_RoomsAndWalls_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:cb4fcdf4ce1cebaf</T>
      <T n="text">0xF448941B<!--String: "You can also create an <b><font color='#199C2C'>Empty Room</font></b> by selecting one of the presets from the catalog and placing it on your Lot. \nThis is the only way to create a <b><font color='#199C2C'>Rounded Room</font></b>."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\BuildMode\BuildMode_RoomsAndWalls_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:cb4fcdf4ce1ceba8</T>
      <T n="text">0xA92B85A3<!--String: "You can <b><font color='#199C2C'>move</font></b>, <b><font color='#199C2C'>resize</font></b>, and <b><font color='#199C2C'>rotate</font></b> an existing Room by selecting it with the Select tool and clicking the Buttons that appear. You can also rotate a Room by moving it and using the [&lt;] and [&gt;] keys on the keyboard.\n\nThis will also display the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Wall Height</font></b> options. All Walls on the same Floor will have the same Wall Height. Certain structures such as Windows and Friezes may have a minimum Wall Height. They will be removed if the Wall Height is shortened to below that minimum."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\BuildMode\BuildMode_RoomsAndWalls_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:cb4fcdf4ce1ceba9</T>
      <T n="text">0x94A007AC<!--String: "<b><font color='#199C2C'>Delete a Room</font></b> with the Sledgehammer tool, or selecting it with the Select tool and pressing the [Del] key on the keyboard.\n\nYou can also <b><font color='#199C2C'>delete an individual wall</font></b> by clicking and dragging with the Wall Tool while holding down the [Ctrl] key."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\BuildMode\BuildMode_RoomsAndWalls_6.png">2f7d0004:00000000:cb4fcdf4ce1cebaa</T>
      <T n="text">0x8F5875E<!--String: "When manipulating Rooms and Walls, you may notice <b><font color='#199C2C'>green</font></b> and <b><font color='#199C2C'>yellow</font></b> highlights.\n\nGreen indicates the wall has passed through architecture that will be modified in some way.\nYellow indicates an object that will be moved to the Household Inventory, or sold."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
